research_objectives:
1. How do horoscopes (daily) with actual english prompts perform?
  2. How well do they meet the new topics? In comparison to originals?
research_findings:
The results of this round are clearly in favour of the generated horoscopes from davinci compared to human written horoscope texts in English.
Differences are subtle but consistent and significant except for grammar. Only some minor orthography mistakes have been made. For the davinci this was due to a bug ("Aries" proper name in "bounaries" spelled "boundAries").

Meaning, English prompts for daily horoscopes work very well with the used davinci model and outperform even human written texts. The reviewers did not seem to make a "generated vs. human written" distinction between the two lists.
